              <title>Multilevel Marketing techniques for scaling MOOCs</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7386</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7386</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>How can 1000s of learners be supported in MOOCs that become <strong>massive</strong>?</p>
<p><strong><a title="Multi-level Marketing" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multi-level_marketing#Setup">Multi-level Marketing</a></strong>&nbsp;techniques - newbies would sign up and be given a number of tokens/coins. They would offer to pay a coach/mentor/teacher coins in order to master a particular competency. Eventually they would advance into the mentor-coach role and pay their former mentor coach for back-up or support. The more one helps, the more one is paid.</p>
<p>Helpers reputation rank might even allow them to raise their fees, lol.</p>]]></description>
