              <title>Proposal of a new kind of a wiki history</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/647</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/647</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>
If you work on a large text collaboratively with a lot of contributers you can have a look at the history to see the contributions but you have to decide whether to look what a single person changed or to look what is changed without to see who changed it (when you don't want to follow every little contribution). It would be great to have a wiki with a modified history which indicates the changed parts with colours and the changing person in a context menu when clicking on the colored part. The color could indicate how old the change is and move to black over time.
</p>
<p>
