              <title>Using LAMS for collaborative learning</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/578</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/578</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>
Nagoya Bunri Univerisity is first LAMS user for education in Japan
</p>
<p>
&nbsp;
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Use of LAMS to design and deliver a colllaborative learning activity. </li>
	<li>10 students over three weeks.</li>
	<li>The course was a basic seminar course for computer/information ethics study</li>
	<li>LAMS was used to research and disucss on computer crimes.</li>
	<li>3 sequences 1. file sharing software (Winny), 2. electronic bulletin board, 3. hazardous sites</li>
	<li>All students worked together on each actiivity at the same time.</li>
	<li>Learning process: web search, exchange info, exchange opinions</li>
	<li>Gates were allocated after every activity and the teacher controled the sequence flow.</li>
	<li>90% of students were positive about using LAMS in terms of its usability, interest</li>
	<li>and comprehension.</li>
	<li>In future they may allow students to go freely to the next step</li>
	<li>The teacher intervened in the discussion with the students</li>
