              <description><![CDATA[This BA programme in Child and Youth Studies is delivered to rural communities in the Scottish Highlands, where face-to-face contact between learners, peers and tutors is necessarily low, and its place is taken by well-managed online discussion.

The key design features are: (1) a link with assessment (discussion contributions count for 25% of module marks); (2) use of appropriate technology (synchronous real-time chat for small group tutorial sessions, asynchronous discussion boards for more reflective collaboration); (3) careful moderation by tutors; and (4) diagnostic pre-assessment of students’ ICT skills, followed by training if necessary.

