                    <item>
              <title>Interactive posters and presentations</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/25</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/25</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[In Chemistry one way in which we used to make teaching some of the boring mundane aspects of the subject was through the use of interactive posters coupled with a group presentation. Students are allocated into groups. Each group was given an element to research. They divided the different aspects up - structure, properties, chemical reactions, medicinal and industrial use etc. Over a period of a month they researched the topic coming together to share progress from time to time. I provided support in terms of how to find and interpret information. The goal was to produce individual posters on each area and a group presentation. The final session was attended by other students and staff and both the posters and presentations were peer marked. Posters then acted as a valuable resource for the next cohort of students. The students rated the experience highly and gained general ICT and study skills as well as learning about the main topic.   ]]></description>
